This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it presents an online platform for story understanding built on top of a reasoning engine. It also discusses ongoing work on adding new features and functionality to the platform, which suggests a focus on natural language processing and computational linguistics. Additionally, the paper mentions integration with other systems, which could involve machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The platform also includes social features, such as collaboration tools and a commenting system, which could fall under the sub-categories of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper discusses the use of a web-based IDE, which could involve aspects of machine learning and data analysis, potentially placing it in the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG).
